         <abstract><p>Hymn composed on the occasion of the consecration of the church of Dabra Bǝrhān Śǝllāse (1694 A.D.) and attributed to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8671SebhatL">ʾAbbā Sǝbḥat Laʾab</persName> (†1702 A.D.).</p>
            <p>According to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/X4SBAXAT"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Loefgren1974Katalog"/><title level="m">Katalog über die äthiopischen Handschriften in der Universitätsbibliothek Uppsala, Sowie Anhänge über äthiopische Handschriften in anderen Bibliotheken und in Privatbesitz in Schweden</title><title level="s">Acta Bibliothecae R. Universitatis Upsaliensis</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Oscar</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Löfgren</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Uppsala</pubPlace><publisher>Almqvist &amp; Wiksell</publisher><date>1974</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Acta Bibliothecae R. Universitatis Upsaliensis</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">18</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">18</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">45</citedRange></bibl>,
               the text was written under one <foreign xml:lang="gez-tr">nǝguś</foreign> ʾIyāsu mentioned in the 
               <foreign xml:lang="gez-tr">malkǝʾ</foreign>, i.e. either under 
               <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5616IyasuI">ʾIyāsu I (r. 1682–1706)</persName> or
               <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5617IyasuII">ʾIyāsu II (r. 1730–1755)</persName>.</p>
         </abstract>
